@dev See {IERC1155MetadataURI-uri}.

addACManufacturer(address).details: add/remove a account as the role of `AC_MANUFACTURER` and `AS_MANUFACTURER`. Requirements: - the caller must have the `MANUFACTURER`.

addDesignDrawings(string).details: Update design drawing . Requirements: - the caller must have the `DESIGNER`.

addDesigner(address).details: add/remove a account as the role of `DESIGNER`. Requirements: - the caller must have the `OWNER`.

addJDesigner(address).details: add/remove a account as the role of `J_DESIGNER` and `S_DESIGNER`. Requirements: - the caller must have the `DESIGNER`.

addMaintainer(address).details: add/remove a account as the role of `MAINTAINER`. Requirements: - the caller must have the `OWNER`.

addMaintenanceLogs(string).details: Update maintenance logs . Requirements: - the caller must have the `MAINTAINER`.

addManufacturer(address).details: add/remove a account as the role of `MANUFACTURER`. Requirements: - the caller must have the `OWNER`.

addManufacturingProgress(string).details: Update manufacturing progress . Requirements: - the caller must have the `MANUFACTURER`.

addOServicer(address).details: add/remove a account as the role of `O_SERVICER` and `T_SERVICER`. Requirements: - the caller must have the `SERVICER`.

addRecycler(address).details: add/remove a account as the role of `RECYCLER`. Requirements: - the caller must have the `OWNER`.

addServiceLogs(string).details: Update service logs . Requirements: - the caller must have the `SERVICER`.

addServicer(address).details: add/remove a account as the role of SERVICER`. Requirements: - the caller must have the `OWNER`.

balanceOf(address,uint256).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOf}. Requirements: - `account` cannot be the zero address.

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOfBatch}. Requirements: - `accounts` and `ids` must have the same length.

exists(uint256).details: Indicates whether the specified `tokenId` exists or not.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getRoleMember(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns one of the accounts that have `role`. `index` must be a value between 0 and {getRoleMemberCount}, non-inclusive. Role bearers are not sorted in any particular way, and their ordering may change at any point. WARNING: When using {getRoleMember} and {getRoleMemberCount}, make sure you perform all queries on the same block. See the following https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/iterating-over-elements-on-enumerableset-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2296[forum post] for more information.

getRoleMemberCount(bytes32).details: Returns the number of accounts that have `role`. Can be used together with {getRoleMember} to enumerate all bearers of a role.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

mint(address,uint256,bytes).details: Creates `amount` new NFT for `to`, of token type `id`. See {ERC1155-_mint}. Requirements: - the caller must have the `RECYCLER`.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

setURI(string).details: Update the URI for all tokens. Requirements: - the caller must have the `OWNER`.

tokenByIndex(uint256).details: Returns the `index`-th tokenId stored by the contract.

tokenCountOf(address).details: Returns the number of token ids held by `owner`.

tokens(uint256,uint256).details: Returns token IDs in pagination view.

tokensOf(address,uint256,uint256).details: Returns token IDs of specified `owner` in pagination view.

totalSupply().details: Returns the number of different tokenIds stored by the contract.

totalSupply(uint256).details: Returns the total amount of tokens for the specified `tokenId`.

updatelife(uint256).details: Update the life cycle phase of the digital twin. Requirements: - the caller must have the `OWNER`.

uri(uint256).details: See {IERC1155MetadataURI-uri}. This implementation returns the same URI for *all* token types. It relies on the token type ID substitution mechanism https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1155#metadata[defined in the EIP]. Clients calling this function must replace the `\{id\}` substring with the actual token type ID.
